The goal is to leak the file contents character by character based on the reaction to an error (DownUnderCTF minimal-php).
• convert.iconv:// - recoding into another charset (for example convert.iconv.utf-16le.utf-8).
• dechunk:// - if a string has no line breaks, it is erased entirely if and only if it starts with A-Fa-f0-9.
Requirements:
• the backend does not use file_exists / is_file;
• the vulnerable parameter is in a POST request (in GET you cannot leak more than 135 characters due to the size limit).
Chain logic:
1) iconv with a charset that exponentially increases the data size -> memory error;
2) dechunk determines the first character of the file by the presence/absence of an error;
3) iconv with a different byte order swaps the remaining characters with the first one.
